Identification of environmental impactsboth positive and/or negativemust involve:
(1) Identifying each specific risk or impact;
(2) Classifying each as positive, negative, or neutral, with justification for the classification;
(3) Explaining the measures to avoid, reduce, mitigate, or compensate for any negative impacts;
(4) Outlining how the risks and impacts will be monitored, including the frequency and responsible parties; and
(5) Optionally, describing how positive impacts contribute to the Sustainable Development Goals.
